Sentencas: Ru/Nb co-doped (Pr0.5Sr0.5)(0.9)Fe0.8Ru0.1Nb0.1O3-delta (PSFRN) cubic perovskite oxide was fabricated and used as the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode material.
Titulo: Ru/Nb co-doped perovskite anode: Achieving good coking resistance in hydrocarbon fuels via core-shell nanocatalysts exsolution

Sentencas: After treated in wet H-2 at 900 degrees C for 2 h, the PSFRN was partially transformed into Ruddlesden-Popper (RP) layered perovskite PrSrFe0.8Ru0.1Nb0.1O4+delta (RP-PSFRN), and Fe0.7Ru0.3 alloy-FeOx oxide (FRA@FO) core-shell nanoparticles were in-situ exsolved on the reduced-PSFRN (R-PSFRN) substrate surface.
Titulo: Ru/Nb co-doped perovskite anode: Achieving good coking resistance in hydrocarbon fuels via core-shell nanocatalysts exsolution

Sentencas: The phase transition and the exsolution of the nanoparticles were investigated using X-ray diffraction, transmission electron microscope and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy.
Titulo: Ru/Nb co-doped perovskite anode: Achieving good coking resistance in hydrocarbon fuels via core-shell nanocatalysts exsolution

Sentencas: Modified by the in-situ exsolved FRA@FO core-shell nanoparticles, the R-PSFRN anode material showed high catalytic activity for hydrogen and hydrocarbon fuels.
Titulo: Ru/Nb co-doped perovskite anode: Achieving good coking resistance in hydrocarbon fuels via core-shell nanocatalysts exsolution

Sentencas: The power density of SOFC reached 0.683 and 0.537 W cm(-2) with wet H-2 and C3H8 as fuel at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Ru/Nb co-doped perovskite anode: Achieving good coking resistance in hydrocarbon fuels via core-shell nanocatalysts exsolution

Sentencas: Moreover, the SOFC showed a stable output under a constant current load of 0.15 A cm(-2) in C3H8, demonstrating a high resistance to carbon deposition and coking.
Titulo: Ru/Nb co-doped perovskite anode: Achieving good coking resistance in hydrocarbon fuels via core-shell nanocatalysts exsolution
